{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:psalms.77",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 77,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 77 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:1",
      "text": "A Psalm of instruction for Asaph. - Give heed, O my people, to my law: incline your ear to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:2",
      "text": "I will open my mouth in parables: I will utter dark sayings which have been from the beginning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:3",
      "text": "All which we have heard and known, and our fathers have declared to us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:4",
      "text": "They were not hid from their children to a second generations; the fathers declaring the praises of the Lord, and his mighty acts, and his wonders which he wrought.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:5",
      "text": "And he raised up a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, to make it known to their children:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:6",
      "text": "that another generation might know, even the sons which should be born; and they should arise and declare them to their children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:7",
      "text": "That they might set their hope on God, and not forget the works of God, but diligently seek his commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:8",
      "text": "That they should not be as their fathers, a perverse and provoking generation; a generation which set not its heart aright, and its spirit was not steadfast with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:9",
      "text": "The children of Ephraim, bending and shooting with the bow, turned back in the day of battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:10",
      "text": "They kept not the covenant of God, and would not walk in his law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:11",
      "text": "And they forgot his benefits, and his miracles which he had shewed them;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:12",
      "text": "the miracles which he wrought before their fathers, in the land of Egypt, in the plain of Tanes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:13",
      "text": "He clave the sea, and led them through: he made the waters to stand as in a bottle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:14",
      "text": "And he guided them with a cloud by day, and all the night with a light of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:15",
      "text": "he clave a rock in the wilderness, and made them drink as in a great deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:16",
      "text": "And he brought water out of the rock, and caused waters to flow down as rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:17",
      "text": "And they sinned yet more against him; they provoked the Most High in the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:18",
      "text": "And they tempted God in their hearts, in asking meat for the desire of their souls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:19",
      "text": "They spoke also against God, and said, Will God be able to prepare a table in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:20",
      "text": "Forasmuch as he smote the rock, and the waters flowed, and the torrents ran abundantly; will he be able also to give bread, or prepare a table for his people?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:21",
      "text": "Therefore the Lord heard, and was provoked: and fire was kindled in Jacob, and wrath went up against Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:22",
      "text": "Because they believed not in God, and trusted not in his salvation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:23",
      "text": "Yet he commanded the clouds from above, and opened the doors of heaven,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:24",
      "text": "and rained upon them manna to eat, and gave them the bread of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:25",
      "text": "Man ate angels’ bread; he sent them provision to the full.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:26",
      "text": "He removed the south wind from heaven; and by his might he brought in the south-west wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:27",
      "text": "And he rained upon them flesh like dust, and feathered birds like the sand of the seas.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:28",
      "text": "And they fell into the midst of their camp, round about their tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:29",
      "text": "So they ate, and were completely filled; and he gave them their desire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:30",
      "text": "They were not disappointed of their desire: but when their food was yet in their mouth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:31",
      "text": "then the indignation of God rose up against them, and slew the fattest of them, and overthrew the choice men of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:32",
      "text": "In the midst of all this they sinned yet more, and believed not his miracles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:33",
      "text": "And their days were consumed in vanity, and their years with anxiety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.34",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:34",
      "text": "When he slew them, they sought him: and they returned and called betimes upon God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.35",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:35",
      "text": "And they remembered that God was their helper, and the most high God was their redeemer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.36",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:36",
      "text": "Yet they loved him only with their mouth, and lied to him with their tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.37",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:37",
      "text": "For their heart was not right with him, neither were they steadfast in his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.38",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:38",
      "text": "But he is compassionate, and will forgive their sins, and will not destroy them: yea, he will frequently turn away his wrath, and will not kindle all his anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.39",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:39",
      "text": "And he remembered that they are flesh; a wind that passes away, and returns not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.40",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:40",
      "text": "How often did they provoke him in the wilderness, and anger him in a dry land!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.41",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:41",
      "text": "Yea, they turned back, and tempted God, and provoked the Holy One of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.42",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:42",
      "text": "They remembered not his hand, the day in which he delivered them from the hand of the oppressor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.43",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:43",
      "text": "How he had wrought his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Tanes:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.44",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:44",
      "text": "and had changed their rivers into blood; and their streams, that they should not drink.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.45",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:45",
      "text": "He sent against them the dog-fly, and it devoured them; and the frog, and it spoiled them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.46",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:46",
      "text": "And he gave their fruit to the canker worm, and their labours to the locust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.47",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:47",
      "text": "He killed their vines with hail, and their sycamores with frost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.48",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:48",
      "text": "And he gave up their cattle to hail, and their substance to the fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.49",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:49",
      "text": "He sent out against them the fury of his anger, wrath, and indignation, and affliction, a message by evil angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.50",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:50",
      "text": "He made a way for his wrath; he spared not their souls from death, but consigned their cattle to death;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.51",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:51",
      "text": "and smote every first-born in the land of Egypt; the first-fruits of their labours in the tents of Cham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.52",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:52",
      "text": "And he removed his people like sheep; he led them as a flock in the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.53",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:53",
      "text": "And he guided them with hope, and they feared not: but the sea covered their enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.54",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:54",
      "text": "And he brought them in to the mountain of his sanctuary, this mountain which his right hand had purchased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.55",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:55",
      "text": "And he cast out the nations from before them, and made them to inherit by a line of inheritance, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.56",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:56",
      "text": "Ye they tempted and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.57",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:57",
      "text": "And they turned back, and broke covenant, even as also their fathers: they became like a crooked bow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.58",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:58",
      "text": "And they provoked him with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.59",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:59",
      "text": "God heard and lightly regarded them, and greatly despised Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.60",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:60",
      "text": "And he rejected the tabernacle of Selom, his tent where he dwelt among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.61",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:61",
      "text": "And he gave their strength into captivity, and their beauty into the enemy’s hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.62",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:62",
      "text": "And he gave his people to the sword; and disdained his inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.63",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:63",
      "text": "Fire devoured their young men; and their virgins mourned not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.64",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:64",
      "text": "Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows shall not be wept for.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.65",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:65",
      "text": "So the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and as a mighty man who has been heated with wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.66",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:66",
      "text": "And he smote his enemies in the hinder parts: he brought on them a perpetual reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.77.67",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 77,
      "verseNumber": 67,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 77:67",
